body:
Excellent work by the way - I've just discovered yosys and have been experimenting with the latest win32 binary.

I found out that "abc -liberty mycells.lib" causes yosys to crash if there are any spaces in the path.

I used -nocleanup and -showtmp options to find the following in abc.script within the temporary folder:

echo + read_blif _tmp_yosys-abc-7mN4Hh/input.blif;
read_blif _tmp_yosys-abc-7mN4Hh/input.blif;
echo + read_lib -w C:\Users\Dave user\Desktop\yosys_logic_synthesis\win32_executable\yosys-win32-mxebin-0.7/cmos_cells.lib";
read_lib -w C:\Users\Dave user\Desktop\yosys_logic_synthesis\win32_executable\yosys-win32-mxebin-0.7/cmos_cells.lib";
echo + strash;
strash;
echo + dc2;
dc2;
echo + scorr;
scorr;
echo + ifraig;
ifraig;
echo + retime -o ;
retime -o ;
echo + strash;
strash;
echo + dch -f;
dch -f;
echo + map ;
map ;
echo + write_blif _tmp_yosys-abc-7mN4Hh/output.blif;
write_blif _tmp_yosys-abc-7mN4Hh/output.blif

I tried explicitly specifying the full liberty library path and filename in quotes to no avail.

As soon as I moved everything to a directory/username with no spaces, everything worked perfectly. 

Hopefully this helps anyone else scratching their head with the windows binary - sorry I'm not too hot of a programmer so wouldn't know where to start looking in the code for suggestions.

Thank you very much Clifford et al - very impressive and interesting stuff.
